1
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:19,052
[GOLD ROGER]
Destiny. Fate. Dreams.

2
00:00:19,052 --> 00:00:23,456
These unstoppable ideals are
held deep in the heart of man.

3
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:27,093
As long as there are people
who seek freedom in this life,

4
00:00:27,127 --> 00:00:30,030
these things shall not
vanish from the earth!

5
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,706
<i>♪People tell me my</i>
<i>head's in the clouds</i>

6
00:00:39,739 --> 00:00:41,207
<i>I don't care what they say</i>

7
00:00:41,241 --> 00:00:43,043
<i>because I'm dreamin' of you</i>

8
00:00:43,076 --> 00:00:45,945
<i>You are the treasure I've found</i>

9
00:00:45,979 --> 00:00:48,548
<i>So bright, so bold,</i>
<i>yet so elusive</i>

10
00:00:48,581 --> 00:00:51,251
<i>It's hard to look away,</i>

11
00:00:51,251 --> 00:00:54,287
<i>even though it's blinding me</i>

12
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:55,955
<i>There are no words to describe</i>

13
00:00:55,989 --> 00:00:57,657
<i>how I feel inside</i>

14
00:00:57,724 --> 00:01:01,261
<i>I'm really really stuck</i>
<i>on you whoa, whoa!</i>

15
00:01:01,294 --> 00:01:02,729
<i>I have to follow my dreams</i>

16
00:01:02,762 --> 00:01:04,330
<i>however crazy they seem</i>

17
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:07,600
<i>And I won't stop 'til I</i>
<i>get there, you will see</i>

18
00:01:07,634 --> 00:01:08,968
<i>You're all I need</i>

19
00:01:09,002 --> 00:01:11,137
<i>to have the strength to believe</i>

20
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:17,277
<i>Believe in Wonderland!</i>

21
00:01:19,779 --> 00:01:21,414
<i>I'm gonna follow my dreams,</i>

22
00:01:21,448 --> 00:01:23,083
<i>however crazy they seem</i>

23
00:01:23,116 --> 00:01:24,484
<i>I'm gonna share them with you,</i>

24
00:01:24,517 --> 00:01:26,186
<i>a love so true</i>

25
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:29,589
<i>You're all I want,</i>
<i>together we can move on</i>

26
00:01:29,622 --> 00:01:32,192
<i>Live how we want to!</i>

27
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:33,626
<i>There is no limit to us,</i>

28
00:01:33,660 --> 00:01:35,295
<i>we have the power of love</i>

29
00:01:35,328 --> 00:01:38,465
<i>And we don't wanna</i>
<i>live ordinary lives</i>

30
00:01:38,498 --> 00:01:42,135
<i>We have the chance</i>
<i>to live in paradise</i>

31
00:01:42,135 --> 00:01:47,373
<i>Believe in Wonderland!♪</i>

32
00:01:54,848 --> 00:01:56,783
[KUREHA]
Now have a safe trip...

33
00:01:56,816 --> 00:01:59,552
...my stupid son.

34
00:02:01,855 --> 00:02:03,223
[LUFFY]
"Goodbye Drum Island!

35
00:02:03,223 --> 00:02:05,725
I'm Going Out to Sea!"

36
00:02:12,732 --> 00:02:13,967
‐‐[USOPP] Ooh!
‐‐Whoa!

37
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,202
‐‐[VIVI] It's beautiful!
‐‐[NAMI] Yeah.

38
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:18,805
Like a bunch of cherry blossoms.

39
00:02:21,908 --> 00:02:23,710
Hey, do you think
Chopper's okay?

40
00:02:23,743 --> 00:02:24,911
He's looking a little down.

41
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:25,879
He'll be fine.

42
00:02:25,912 --> 00:02:27,914
Let's just leave him
alone for right now.

43
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:28,882
It's an emotional time.

44
00:02:28,915 --> 00:02:30,884
He's going on his
first journey as a man.

45
00:02:30,917 --> 00:02:33,052
It's a rite of passage.

46
00:02:33,086 --> 00:02:36,489
[VIVI] And he's about to leave
Drum Island behind for good.

47
00:02:36,523 --> 00:02:38,758
It's been his home
his entire life.

48
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:40,527
[USOPP]
Yeah...

49
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:43,730
I'm leaving them,
both Doctor and Doctorine.

50
00:02:43,763 --> 00:02:46,166
My adventure is
finally starting...

51
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:49,102
...right now, on this ship.

52
00:02:54,207 --> 00:02:59,212
[LUFFY, ZORO, USOPP, SANJI
cheering, laughing]

53
00:03:01,881 --> 00:03:03,016
Oh, yeah! Partay!

54
00:03:03,049 --> 00:03:06,052
And these cherry blossoms
are like party decorations.

55
00:03:06,085 --> 00:03:07,921
Come on, Chopper,
snap out of it!

56
00:03:07,954 --> 00:03:10,790
You can't just sit there in a
daze all night long, you know.

57
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:11,758
[LUFFY]
Woo‐hoo!

58
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:13,293
You wanna drink?

59
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:15,728
Come sing a song with us.

60
00:03:15,762 --> 00:03:18,131
[LUFFY] Here! Shove these
chopsticks up your nose.

61
00:03:18,131 --> 00:03:18,932
Go on.

62
00:03:18,965 --> 00:03:20,533
[SANJI]
It's a great moonlit night

63
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:21,901
and cherry blossoms
are in the air.

64
00:03:21,935 --> 00:03:24,604
How could we not party?

65
00:03:24,637 --> 00:03:26,072
‐‐[CHOPPER gasps]
‐‐They're a handful.

66
00:03:26,105 --> 00:03:27,807
I hate to tell you,
but your new friends

67
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:30,243
are about as crazy as they come.

68
00:03:31,244 --> 00:03:33,146
My... friends?

69
00:03:33,146 --> 00:03:35,882
That's right. These guys can
really be a lot to handle,

70
00:03:35,915 --> 00:03:36,983
but now that you're one of us,

71
00:03:36,983 --> 00:03:39,285
you're gonna have to
get used to it.

72
00:03:40,987 --> 00:03:42,889
Karoo! What in the
world were you doing

73
00:03:42,922 --> 00:03:44,757
frozen in the river like that?!

74
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:46,626
[squawking]

75
00:03:46,659 --> 00:03:49,729
That bird! Ten Berries says he
slipped and fell into the river.

76
00:03:49,762 --> 00:03:50,763
He's a clumsy one.

77
00:03:50,797 --> 00:03:52,966
[VIVI]
Be quiet, Mr. Bushido.

78
00:03:52,999 --> 00:03:54,767
‐‐[KAROO squawks]
‐‐[CHOPPER] Uh‐huh, yeah...

79
00:03:54,801 --> 00:03:56,002
He said that the guy named Zoro

80
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:57,837
was swimming in the river
and disappeared.

81
00:03:57,837 --> 00:03:59,005
He thought Zoro
was in trouble,

82
00:03:59,005 --> 00:04:00,607
so he jumped into
the river to help

83
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:01,975
and ended up getting
frozen in it.

84
00:04:02,008 --> 00:04:03,676
So this is all your fault!

85
00:04:03,676 --> 00:04:04,777
[ZORO]
Ow...

86
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:06,346
So you were really
able to understand

87
00:04:06,346 --> 00:04:08,014
everything Karoo was saying?

88
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:10,817
Yes. I'm still technically
half animal by nature,

89
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:12,685
so I can understand
what they say.

90
00:04:12,685 --> 00:04:14,153
You can talk to animals?

91
00:04:14,187 --> 00:04:15,255
Oh, wow, Chopper!

92
00:04:15,288 --> 00:04:17,657
Between your medical skills
and talking to animals,

93
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,158
you've got some
amazing talents.

94
00:04:19,192 --> 00:04:20,026
[gasps]

95
00:04:20,026 --> 00:04:20,994
[CHOPPER]
Don't be silly, you jerk!

96
00:04:21,027 --> 00:04:22,762
Flattering me like that
isn't gonna make me

97
00:04:22,795 --> 00:04:24,697
happy or anything!

98
00:04:24,697 --> 00:04:25,932
[LUFFY, USOPP]
He sure looks happy.

99
00:04:25,965 --> 00:04:27,033
Hey, what did you mean about

100
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,968
Chopper's "medical
skills" anyway?

101
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:32,338
Well, Chopper here is a doctor,
and a first‐rate one at that.

102
00:04:32,372 --> 00:04:35,608
Dr. Kureha taught him everything
there is to know about medicine.

103
00:04:35,642 --> 00:04:36,709
[ZORO, LUFFY, USOPP]
Huh?

104
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:37,610
Impossible.

105
00:04:37,644 --> 00:04:39,712
Chopper, are you
seriously a doctor?

106
00:04:39,712 --> 00:04:40,947
How cool!

107
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:41,814
No way!

108
00:04:41,848 --> 00:04:43,716
Really, Luffy,
if you didn't know that,

109
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:46,219
what did you think Chopper was
when you asked him to join us?

110
00:04:46,219 --> 00:04:48,988
A talking, transforming
reindeer monster.

111
00:04:49,022 --> 00:04:51,224
Back up food.

112
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:52,125
[CHOPPER gasps]

113
00:04:52,158 --> 00:04:53,326
Wait! Oh, no!

114
00:04:53,359 --> 00:04:55,895
I was in such a big hurry
I left my medical bag behind!

115
00:04:55,895 --> 00:04:57,230
It had all of my tools in it!

116
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:58,998
Your bag? But isn't this it?

117
00:04:59,032 --> 00:05:00,333
Huh?

118
00:05:00,366 --> 00:05:01,801
That is my bag!

119
00:05:01,834 --> 00:05:04,237
[NAMI] It was in
the back of the sleigh.

120
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,872
How is that?

121
00:05:05,905 --> 00:05:06,839
[NAMI]
What do you mean?

122
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:08,174
Weren't you the one
who packed the sleigh

123
00:05:08,207 --> 00:05:10,310
and got it ready for the trip?

124
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:13,579
[CHOPPER gasps]

125
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,910
[NAMI]
That's amazing.

126
00:05:43,943 --> 00:05:46,279
Doctorine must have known
what you were planning to do

127
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:50,116
even before you had decided
to leave the island with us.

128
00:05:51,451 --> 00:05:53,286
[NAMI]
What a kind woman.

129
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,087
Yes.

130
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,755
[SANJI, ZORO, USOPP]
Woo! Yeah!

131
00:05:55,788 --> 00:05:58,858
[LUFFY laughs]
Here. Eat it! Usopp, eat it!

132
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:02,261
[LUFFY, SANJI, ZORO, USOPP
laughing, chattering]

133
00:06:02,295 --> 00:06:04,063
Those guys.
Can't they see you're

134
00:06:04,097 --> 00:06:07,734
having a sentimental moment
here? I'm sorry, Chopper.

135
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:08,968
Chopper?

136
00:06:08,968 --> 00:06:10,870
You, too?!

137
00:06:12,071 --> 00:06:13,940
[USOPP]
All right, Straw Hat Crew!

138
00:06:13,973 --> 00:06:15,308
Attention!

139
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:17,443
Listen, all of you!

140
00:06:17,477 --> 00:06:20,813
[BOTH yelling]

141
00:06:20,813 --> 00:06:22,382
[USOPP] ...half man.
Introducing Tony Chopper!

142
00:06:22,415 --> 00:06:24,917
Come on, Sanji!

143
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:27,420
Hey, you know...

144
00:06:27,453 --> 00:06:29,122
Come on, you guys.

145
00:06:29,155 --> 00:06:31,157
Listen up right now!

146
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:32,825
They're crazy.

147
00:06:32,825 --> 00:06:35,328
[KAROO squawking]

148
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:38,464
[USOPP, ZORO, SANJI yelling]

149
00:06:38,498 --> 00:06:41,067
But I've never had
this much fun ever!

150
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:43,002
Good!

151
00:06:43,002 --> 00:06:46,105
I propose a toast to
our new friend, Chopper!

152
00:06:46,139 --> 00:06:48,074
[ALL]
Yeah!

153
00:06:48,107 --> 00:06:50,943
Chopper!

154
00:06:50,977 --> 00:06:52,979
[ALL laughing]

155
00:06:57,984 --> 00:07:00,353
[DALTON] I wonder if they've
made it off the island yet.

156
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:01,921
You know, that reindeer
friend of yours

157
00:07:01,954 --> 00:07:04,857
is a first‐rate doctor
with a first‐rate heart.

158
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:06,692
I'm very glad to have known him.

159
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:08,428
[KUREHA] Those cherry
blossoms of Hiriluk's

160
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:11,264
really did lead to
something miraculous.

161
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:12,331
[KUREHA chuckles]

162
00:07:12,365 --> 00:07:13,833
[KUREHA] But who'd have
thought the miracle would be

163
00:07:13,866 --> 00:07:15,868
that clumsy reindeer
going out to sea

164
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:19,105
with a group of
pirates? That kid...

165
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:22,275
...acting like he's a
grown man all of a sudden.

166
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:25,778
I have a feeling he'll
make a fine ship's doctor.

167
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:26,813
So what are your plans

168
00:07:26,846 --> 00:07:30,783
now that Wapol is gone
from the island for good?

169
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:32,785
For a long time...

170
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,053
...I worked as the
captain of the guard

171
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,789
under Wapol's tyrannical rule.

172
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:40,026
That's something that I still
need to make amends for.

173
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:42,295
I was thinking about
leaving this country‐‐

174
00:07:42,328 --> 00:07:44,797
trusting the citizens to make
a better land for themselves

175
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:46,833
without me here as a reminder.

176
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:48,501
[KUREHA]
I see.

177
00:07:48,534 --> 00:07:51,137
Is that what you've
decided to do?

178
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:52,472
[DALTON]
No.

179
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:53,806
I realize that leaving here

180
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:56,843
isn't the way to make up
for past mistakes.

181
00:07:56,876 --> 00:07:59,479
This country is rid of
it's corrupt monarchy.

182
00:07:59,512 --> 00:08:01,013
It's citizens are
preparing to build

183
00:08:01,047 --> 00:08:03,316
a new country
that's all their own.

184
00:08:03,349 --> 00:08:05,218
And I think if I stayed here,

185
00:08:05,251 --> 00:08:06,819
I could find a way
to help them build it

186
00:08:06,853 --> 00:08:09,322
into the country
that it's meant to be.

187
00:08:09,355 --> 00:08:11,090
Maybe that will help...

188
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:12,358
...by washing away
some of the guilt

189
00:08:12,391 --> 00:08:14,994
that I've carried around
with me for so long.

190
00:08:15,027 --> 00:08:17,029
Well, seems to me...

191
00:08:17,063 --> 00:08:19,232
...that you certainly do
possess the strength of heart

192
00:08:19,265 --> 00:08:22,068
to take care of this country.

193
00:08:22,101 --> 00:08:25,338
Strength of heart is needed
to look after a country.

194
00:08:25,371 --> 00:08:27,173
And it can be
difficult to come by,

195
00:08:27,206 --> 00:08:28,207
but I once saw it from a girl

196
00:08:28,241 --> 00:08:31,110
who was no more than
ten years old at the time.

197
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:33,779
[WAPOL groans]
The World Summit again.

198
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:35,181
What a useless event this is.

199
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:37,083
I'm tired of coming to
this thing every year.

200
00:08:37,116 --> 00:08:39,352
[KUROMARIMO]
You're absolutely right, sir.

201
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:41,687
[DALTON]
I wonder how much longer

202
00:08:41,687 --> 00:08:44,524
Drum Kingdom can
continue like this.

203
00:08:44,557 --> 00:08:48,861
The rift between the monarchy
and the citizens keeps growing.

204
00:08:48,895 --> 00:08:49,795
[PERSON A gasps]

205
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:52,398
[PERSON A]
Look! It's the king of Alabasta!

206
00:08:52,431 --> 00:08:54,800
[PERSON C]
Cobra Nefertari!

207
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,905
A king who is known
throughout the world

208
00:08:58,938 --> 00:09:01,307
for his benevolence and wisdom.

209
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,076
[KING A]
The revolutionist, Dragon‐‐

210
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:06,946
this man's beliefs
are very dangerous.

211
00:09:06,979 --> 00:09:08,948
As world leaders,
we should be aware

212
00:09:08,981 --> 00:09:11,217
of the threat he poses
to our countries.

213
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:13,085
In as little as
five or six years,

214
00:09:13,119 --> 00:09:15,154
he will likely become
a prominent enemy

215
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,223
opposed to our interests.

216
00:09:17,256 --> 00:09:18,424
[yawns]

217
00:09:18,457 --> 00:09:20,993
Well, I don't know about the
rest of your dumb countries,

218
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:23,596
but mine's governed too well for
my citizens to be lead astray

219
00:09:23,629 --> 00:09:25,898
by some revolutionist. [yawns]

220
00:09:25,932 --> 00:09:28,301
Go ahead and capture him if
you want, but leave me out.

221
00:09:28,334 --> 00:09:29,402
it's ridiculous.

222
00:09:29,435 --> 00:09:30,469
[COBRA growls]
Fool!

223
00:09:30,503 --> 00:09:32,405
You are a selfish fool!

224
00:09:32,438 --> 00:09:34,073
Why do you think we've
all gathered here

225
00:09:34,106 --> 00:09:35,308
at the World Summit?

226
00:09:35,341 --> 00:09:38,344
‐‐[WAPOL growls]
‐‐Just act responsibly for once!

227
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:41,080
No one talks to me like that!

228
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:43,583
Well, that summit
was as unenjoyable

229
00:09:43,616 --> 00:09:45,084
as all the rest of them.

230
00:09:45,117 --> 00:09:47,587
Huh? That girl!

231
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:50,289
She's that idiot
Cobra's daughter.

232
00:09:50,323 --> 00:09:53,025
[chuckles]

233
00:09:53,826 --> 00:09:55,962
Oh, no! My hand
must have slipped!

234
00:09:55,995 --> 00:09:56,996
What are you doing?!

235
00:09:57,029 --> 00:09:58,264
‐‐Sorry! Ha, ha, ha!
‐‐[IGARAM] Princess Vivi!

236
00:09:58,297 --> 00:09:59,532
Oh, excuse me.

237
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:02,868
If I'm not mistaken, you're the
princess of Alabasta Kingdom.

238
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:05,471
Wow! it must suck to have
such a pathetic father!

239
00:10:05,504 --> 00:10:07,206
Damn it! What do you
think you're doing?!

240
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,641
[VIVI]
No, stop, Igaram.

241
00:10:08,674 --> 00:10:11,210
I'm fine.

242
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:12,378
My apologies.

243
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:14,146
I didn't look where
I was going, sir.

244
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:16,182
‐‐[WAPOL grunts]
‐‐[IGARAM growls]

245
00:10:16,215 --> 00:10:18,117
That is quite a child.

246
00:10:18,150 --> 00:10:19,285
At a World Summit like this

247
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:21,120
where all of the most powerful
leaders are gathered,

248
00:10:21,153 --> 00:10:22,188
tensions tend to run high.

249
00:10:22,221 --> 00:10:24,457
The slightest argument
can trigger an all out war.

250
00:10:24,490 --> 00:10:27,293
Knowing that, she refused
to make a scene.

251
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:31,163
[DALTON]
She's so young to be so wise.

252
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:32,965
[WAPOL]
What an annoying little brat!

253
00:10:32,999 --> 00:10:35,301
Let's go, Dalton.

254
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:36,636
Forgive us.

255
00:10:38,337 --> 00:10:40,573
[VIVI cries]

256
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,142
[VIVI]
It hurts!

257
00:10:43,175 --> 00:10:46,912
You made me so proud today,
Princess Vivi.

258
00:10:48,014 --> 00:10:51,350
[DALTON] That princess had
great strength of heart indeed.

259
00:10:51,384 --> 00:10:53,419
And that hasn't changed.

260
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:56,322
She's remained strong
all these years.

261
00:10:57,556 --> 00:10:59,992
[DALTON]
She would make anyone proud.

262
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:04,563
[DOCTOR A]
Dalton, please.

263
00:11:04,597 --> 00:11:06,165
The desire to care
for our country

264
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:08,167
hasn't faded from
within us either.

265
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,669
Allow us to do something.

266
00:11:09,702 --> 00:11:12,505
We want to help
build a new country.

267
00:11:18,577 --> 00:11:19,779
[DALTON]
Hiriluk.

268
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:23,349
This country will be reborn
as you always wished it to be.

269
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:25,685
Just like your son, Chopper.

270
00:11:25,718 --> 00:11:27,687
[VILLAGER A]
Dalton! You need to hear this.

271
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,622
‐‐[footsteps]
‐‐[VILLAGER A panting]

272
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:31,390
I just remembered
something important

273
00:11:31,424 --> 00:11:32,425
that I forgot to tell you.

274
00:11:32,458 --> 00:11:33,359
What is it?

275
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:35,261
Take a look at this.

276
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:37,530
[VILLAGER B]
It's him!

277
00:11:37,563 --> 00:11:40,199
That's the Straw Hat pirate
who defeated Wapol.

278
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:41,367
We're sure of it!

279
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:44,370
You mean he has a 30‐million‐
Berry bounty on his head?

280
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:45,404
Are you certain?

281
00:11:45,438 --> 00:11:46,539
Goodness.

282
00:11:46,572 --> 00:11:49,642
They're quite a band of rouges,
aren't they. [chuckles]

283
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:51,143
Where'd you find this?

284
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:52,211
Well, uh,

285
00:11:52,244 --> 00:11:54,113
I completely forgot to
report this to you, Dalton.

286
00:11:54,146 --> 00:11:55,481
I'm very sorry.

287
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:58,250
I guess it all happened
about a week ago.

288
00:11:58,284 --> 00:12:00,386
A man who seemed to be
a random traveler

289
00:12:00,419 --> 00:12:03,456
showed up one day
over in Robelle Town.

290
00:12:03,489 --> 00:12:06,759
Strangely, it was a day
without any snowfall.

291
00:12:06,792 --> 00:12:09,328
[VILLAGER B] We have no idea
where on the island he landed.

292
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,564
[VILLAGER A]
Anyway, he told us something.

293
00:12:11,597 --> 00:12:13,466
The man said he was
hunting down Blackbeard,

294
00:12:13,499 --> 00:12:16,502
the pirate who recently attacked
our island with his men.

295
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,237
And then, once he realized

296
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:20,306
that Blackbeard had
already left, he said...

297
00:12:20,339 --> 00:12:22,508
In that case,
I have one more question.

298
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:26,412
Has a pirate wearing a straw hat
come through this area recently?

299
00:12:26,445 --> 00:12:27,646
[VILLAGER B]
We didn't know so

300
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:30,249
he showed us the
wanted poster and said...

301
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:34,420
[ACE] Well, if the guy I
described does show up...

302
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,621
If he does?

303
00:12:35,654 --> 00:12:36,822
[ACE]
Deliver this message:

304
00:12:36,856 --> 00:12:41,293
I will wait for him in Alabasta
for ten days and no more.

305
00:12:41,327 --> 00:12:42,695
Don't forget.

306
00:12:43,496 --> 00:12:48,434
[gasps] Hey! Hold on a sec!
You didn't tell us your name!

307
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:51,537
[ACE]
Oh, yes, I forgot about that.

308
00:12:52,705 --> 00:12:54,273
The name's Ace, gentlemen.

309
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:55,641
If you tell the
Straw Hat pirate,

310
00:12:55,674 --> 00:12:58,310
then he'll know who I am.

311
00:12:58,344 --> 00:13:00,179
[ACE chuckles]

312
00:13:03,516 --> 00:13:04,517
Hey! Catch that guy.

313
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:06,819
He ate and didn't pay his
tab at the restaurant.

314
00:13:06,852 --> 00:13:09,622
[ACE] Just give him
the message, thanks!

315
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:12,658
[BOTH]
Huh...

316
00:13:12,691 --> 00:13:17,396
[DALTON] So he'll be waiting
in Alabasta for ten days. Huh.

317
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:20,633
Hm? Excuse me, Doctor,
but is there something wrong?

318
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:22,067
You look puzzled.

319
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:23,068
Tell me something, Dalton.

320
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:25,838
Have you ever heard of
the man Gol D. Roger?

321
00:13:25,871 --> 00:13:27,506
Gol D.?

322
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:29,375
Do you mean Gold Roger?

323
00:13:29,408 --> 00:13:30,576
I guess.

324
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:33,078
Is that what he goes by now?

325
00:13:33,879 --> 00:13:36,182
[KUREHA]
From the looks of this...

326
00:13:36,215 --> 00:13:37,716
...the guy Chopper
left this island

327
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,652
and headed out to sea with...

328
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:42,321
...is no ordinary pirate.

329
00:13:42,354 --> 00:13:45,157
The spirit of D...

330
00:13:45,191 --> 00:13:46,725
It still lives.

331
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:50,696
Whaddya know.

332
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:10,683
[CHOPPER]
This is amazing, Luffy!

333
00:14:10,716 --> 00:14:12,952
The sea seems to go on forever!

334
00:14:13,018 --> 00:14:13,886
Yeah, it's huge!

335
00:14:13,919 --> 00:14:15,621
And pirates are the
ones who get to have

336
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:17,723
great adventures
on it all the time.

337
00:14:17,723 --> 00:14:18,557
Incredible.

338
00:14:18,557 --> 00:14:20,860
Being a pirate
must be really great!

339
00:14:20,893 --> 00:14:22,928
[BOTH gasp]

340
00:14:22,962 --> 00:14:24,396
[CHOPPER]
Whoa! What is that thing?

341
00:14:24,396 --> 00:14:25,598
[LUFFY]
It's a seagull.

342
00:14:25,631 --> 00:14:28,367
[NAMI] No way. There aren't
any seagulls that are that big.

343
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:31,871
Hey! Seagull!

344
00:14:31,904 --> 00:14:32,805
[NAMI gasps]
It's coming!

345
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:35,474
[LUFFY] See, I was right!
It is a seagull.

346
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:36,909
That's really not
the point right now!

347
00:14:36,942 --> 00:14:38,577
It's coming at us because
you called it...

348
00:14:38,577 --> 00:14:40,646
Oh, yay! Adventure!

349
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:41,914
[screeches]

350
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:44,817
[NAMI yells]

351
00:14:46,418 --> 00:14:47,920
[NAMI]
Hey, where'd Luffy go?

352
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:50,723
‐‐[LUFFY] Yahoo!
‐‐Huh?

353
00:14:50,756 --> 00:14:51,657
You moron!

354
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,993
You're about to become
that bird's dinner!

355
00:14:54,059 --> 00:14:55,961
[CHOPPER] Something horrible
has happened, you guys!

356
00:14:55,995 --> 00:14:57,963
[yells] A bird's eaten Luffy!

357
00:14:57,997 --> 00:14:59,565
This is no time
for playing cards!

358
00:14:59,598 --> 00:15:01,000
We need to do something!
Luffy's in trouble!

359
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:02,902
Did Luffy ask for help?

360
00:15:02,935 --> 00:15:04,003
[CHOPPER]
No...

361
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:05,938
[ZORO] Then there's no problem.
Don't worry about it.

362
00:15:05,938 --> 00:15:07,806
Yeah, but...

363
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:11,777
[LUFFY]
Gum‐Gum...

364
00:15:11,777 --> 00:15:12,811
[LUFFY laughs]

365
00:15:12,845 --> 00:15:14,346
[LUFFY]
...Propeller!

366
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,015
Amazing.

367
00:15:17,349 --> 00:15:19,351
[ALL yell]

368
00:15:19,418 --> 00:15:20,953
[LUFFY grunts]

369
00:15:20,986 --> 00:15:21,654
Hey, Sanji!

370
00:15:21,687 --> 00:15:24,623
I got some meat for us. Look!

371
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:25,991
Why are you guys sleeping?

372
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:27,927
[USOPP, SANJI, ZORO]
We're not, you idiot!

373
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,028
You owe me for this, Luffy.

374
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:30,796
I had a really good hand!

375
00:15:30,829 --> 00:15:32,831
Oh, yeah? Oops. [laughs]

376
00:15:32,865 --> 00:15:34,099
Whoa, that's huge.

377
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,702
Does this mean we can start
having some decent meals now?

378
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:38,604
Can we eat it?

379
00:15:38,637 --> 00:15:41,640
Hey, Chopper,
is something wrong?

380
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,342
Well...

381
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:44,376
...it's just...

382
00:15:44,443 --> 00:15:45,711
...pirates really...

383
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:47,046
You guys really are...

384
00:15:47,112 --> 00:15:48,647
...really incredible!

385
00:15:48,681 --> 00:15:50,549
Why, yes we are!

386
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,384
Hey, listen up you guys!

387
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:53,986
We'll be landing
at Alabasta soon,

388
00:15:54,019 --> 00:15:57,323
and this is no time to be joking
around like a pack of hyenas.

389
00:15:57,356 --> 00:15:58,524
Come on.

390
00:15:58,557 --> 00:16:01,660
[ALL]
Yes, ma'am.

391
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:03,462
[CHOPPER]
So what is Alabasta then?

392
00:16:03,495 --> 00:16:05,497
[NAMI] It's the country
where Vivi's father rules.

393
00:16:05,497 --> 00:16:07,700
[USOPP] Yeah, except there's
this guy named Crocodile

394
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:09,835
who's trying to take over
the country right now.

395
00:16:09,835 --> 00:16:13,005
[SANJI] And Crocodile's one of
the Seven Warlords of the Sea.

396
00:16:13,038 --> 00:16:14,707
Who're those guys?

397
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:16,508
[NAMI] They're pirates
who are given authority

398
00:16:16,508 --> 00:16:17,843
by the World Government.

399
00:16:17,876 --> 00:16:19,979
[CHOPPER] The government
actually supports pirates?

400
00:16:20,012 --> 00:16:21,714
[USOPP]
Yeah. Pretty weird, huh?

401
00:16:21,747 --> 00:16:24,550
And the Seven Warlords
are incredibly powerful.

402
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:27,052
You see, they go around
defeating other pirates,

403
00:16:27,086 --> 00:16:28,187
one by one.

404
00:16:28,187 --> 00:16:31,156
And that's why the government
supports the Warlords.

405
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:33,025
The idea is to have the pirates

406
00:16:33,025 --> 00:16:35,561
get rid of all
the other pirates.

407
00:16:37,062 --> 00:16:39,765
I'm really looking forward to
meeting this Crocodile guy.

408
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:42,067
Crocodile is considered
a hero back home.

409
00:16:42,101 --> 00:16:45,004
He helps get rid of the pirates
who attack Alabasta.

410
00:16:45,037 --> 00:16:47,706
However, his good deeds only
appear good on the surface.

411
00:16:47,706 --> 00:16:49,408
He is an evil man.

412
00:16:49,441 --> 00:16:51,877
In truth, he's manipulating
the citizens of Alabasta

413
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:55,514
to bring about a civil war so
he can take over the country.

414
00:16:55,547 --> 00:16:58,684
No one has realized what
Crocodile's doing yet‐‐

415
00:16:58,717 --> 00:17:01,186
not the people,
not even my father.

416
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:02,855
Right. Well, this should be fun.

417
00:17:02,888 --> 00:17:05,557
All we have to do is
beat up that Crocodile guy.

418
00:17:05,591 --> 00:17:06,925
Yes, but in order to do that,

419
00:17:06,959 --> 00:17:09,028
we have to avert the
civil war in Alabasta

420
00:17:09,061 --> 00:17:11,130
and get Baroque Works
out of the picture.

421
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:12,464
[CHOPPER]
Baroque Works?

422
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:13,799
[USOPP]
Oh, yeah.

423
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:15,734
You don't know anything
about them, either.

424
00:17:15,734 --> 00:17:16,935
To be honest, I don't understand

425
00:17:16,969 --> 00:17:18,437
what's going on
with them myself.

426
00:17:18,470 --> 00:17:19,805
They have a really
complicated system

427
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:21,940
of agents, bosses, and partners.

428
00:17:21,974 --> 00:17:24,576
The system is actually
pretty simple.

429
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:26,578
First, at the very top
of the organization

430
00:17:26,578 --> 00:17:28,447
is the boss, Crocodile.

431
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,749
He's known as Mr. 0.

432
00:17:30,783 --> 00:17:33,052
There are a total of 12
agents and one animal

433
00:17:33,085 --> 00:17:35,721
who receive orders
from the boss directly.

434
00:17:35,754 --> 00:17:37,656
For the most part,
these 12 male agents

435
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:41,160
operate as part of a pair
with a female agent.

436
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:44,763
Mr. 1 is paired with
Miss Double Finger.

437
00:17:44,763 --> 00:17:48,000
Mr. 2 doesn't actually
have a female partner.

438
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:49,802
[ZORO]
Mr. 3 is the candle man

439
00:17:49,835 --> 00:17:51,770
we ran into in
Little Garden, right?

440
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:53,906
[VIVI] That's right,
and his partner is the painter

441
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:54,973
Miss Golden Week.

442
00:17:55,007 --> 00:17:57,776
[NAMI]
Oh, yeah, that little girl.

443
00:17:57,810 --> 00:17:59,645
[VIVI]
Mr. 4 is next in line.

444
00:17:59,678 --> 00:18:01,613
He's paired up with
Miss Merry Christmas.

445
00:18:01,613 --> 00:18:03,916
I don't know much more than
that about those two, though.

446
00:18:03,949 --> 00:18:05,484
[LUFFY]
Then there's that snot guy.

447
00:18:05,517 --> 00:18:06,151
[USOPP]
Mr. 5.

448
00:18:06,185 --> 00:18:06,985
[CHOPPER]
Snot?

449
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:08,087
[USOPP]
Yeah, his snot is explosive.

450
00:18:08,120 --> 00:18:11,490
[VIVI] Mr. 5's entire body
can be used as a weapon.

451
00:18:11,523 --> 00:18:12,925
[NAMI]
His partner, Miss Valentine,

452
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,793
has the Kilo Kilo Fruit powers.

453
00:18:14,793 --> 00:18:16,462
[ZORO] That's the woman
who can change her weight

454
00:18:16,495 --> 00:18:17,863
whenever she wants.

455
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:20,699
[VIVI] The agents with codenames
from Mr. 1 through Mr. 5

456
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,501
are known as officer agents.

457
00:18:22,534 --> 00:18:24,803
They each possess one
of the Devil Fruit powers

458
00:18:24,837 --> 00:18:28,140
and they are only sent on
the most important missions.

459
00:18:28,173 --> 00:18:31,844
Agents Mr. 6 through Mr. 13
have the job of fundraising.

460
00:18:31,877 --> 00:18:33,112
They make money
for the organization

461
00:18:33,145 --> 00:18:36,782
by heading up the employees at
the entrance to the Grand Line.

462
00:18:36,815 --> 00:18:39,118
[SANJI] Hey, what about that
weird monkey and chicken pair

463
00:18:39,151 --> 00:18:39,985
I ran into?

464
00:18:39,985 --> 00:18:43,122
[VIVI]
That's Mr. 13 and Miss Friday.

465
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:45,290
They're the agency's
punishment squad.

466
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:48,494
They punish any agent who
fails to complete a mission.

467
00:18:48,527 --> 00:18:49,661
And there are more.

468
00:18:49,695 --> 00:18:52,164
Under the officer agents are
200 men called "billions."

469
00:18:52,197 --> 00:18:55,033
And there are another 1,800
men under the frontier agents

470
00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:57,302
that are known as "millions."

471
00:18:57,336 --> 00:19:00,839
Together they make up the secret
crime syndicate Baroque Works.

472
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:04,076
Let's see, 200 plus
1,800 equals, um, uh...

473
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,711
There are 2,000 of them?!

474
00:19:05,744 --> 00:19:06,678
Two thousand?!

475
00:19:06,678 --> 00:19:08,914
[LUFFY] All right.
I think I understand.

476
00:19:08,981 --> 00:19:10,649
When are we gonna
get to Alabasta

477
00:19:10,682 --> 00:19:12,184
so I can beat up Crocodile?

478
00:19:12,217 --> 00:19:14,686
Uh, I don't think you
get it at all, Luffy.

479
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:17,756
If Baroque Works' sole objective
is to take over Alabasta,

480
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:19,758
then I can guess
what that must mean.

481
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:22,594
The rest of the officer agents,
as Vivi called them,

482
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:24,696
and their subordinates
are probably...

483
00:19:24,696 --> 00:19:27,900
...on their way to
Alabasta as we speak.

484
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:29,701
Yeah.

485
00:19:29,701 --> 00:19:30,736
[LUFFY]
I see.

486
00:19:30,769 --> 00:19:32,538
So, in that case, we just
go beat up Crocodile...

487
00:19:32,571 --> 00:19:34,907
[SANJI] That's enough,
Luffy. Just let it go.

488
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:36,575
[LUFFY]
Okay...

489
00:19:37,376 --> 00:19:39,211
‐‐[MR. 2] Un...
‐‐[MAN A groaning]

490
00:19:39,244 --> 00:19:40,345
‐‐Deux...
‐‐[MAN A groaning]

491
00:19:40,379 --> 00:19:42,281
‐‐Trois...
‐‐[MAN A groaning]

492
00:19:42,347 --> 00:19:45,951
[MAN A] I'm sorry, Mr. 2,
Mr. Bon Clay, sir...

493
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:48,020
Would you idiots
quit playing around?!

494
00:19:48,053 --> 00:19:49,855
Damn it. Are you
completely clueless?

495
00:19:49,888 --> 00:19:51,256
Do you even know who I am?

496
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:52,391
[groans]

497
00:19:52,424 --> 00:19:55,594
[MR. 2] I am Bon Clay,
a Baroque Works officer agent.

498
00:19:55,627 --> 00:19:58,197
I strike fear into the heart
of anyone who sees me.

499
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:00,299
Hey, you, navigator,
tell me something.

500
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:01,233
Y‐Yes, sir!

501
00:20:01,266 --> 00:20:03,135
[MR. 2] Does that little
pea brain of yours

502
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:05,904
remember what the boss'
exact orders were?

503
00:20:05,904 --> 00:20:07,139
Yes, Mr. 2.

504
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:09,741
The orders were to kill Mr. 3 on
his way along the direct route

505
00:20:09,741 --> 00:20:11,710
between Little Garden
and Alabasta.

506
00:20:11,743 --> 00:20:12,744
Okay, then.

507
00:20:12,778 --> 00:20:15,814
Maybe you're not entirely
useless, now are you?

508
00:20:15,881 --> 00:20:17,082
[MAN A groans]

509
00:20:17,115 --> 00:20:19,651
Taking a direct route means that
you travel in a straight line,

510
00:20:19,718 --> 00:20:20,886
doesn't it, navigator?

511
00:20:20,919 --> 00:20:23,622
That's why we went straight from
Alabasta to Little Garden.

512
00:20:23,655 --> 00:20:25,057
Isn't that right?

513
00:20:25,090 --> 00:20:26,258
‐‐[thudding]
‐‐But then something seems to

514
00:20:26,258 --> 00:20:28,627
